help.groupCode: Code of the group of codes in STD_CODES_GROUP.
help.internalCode: Identifies uniquely an element in a group. Unlike external codes, internal codes are not subject to translation and can therefore be used in programs.
help.startDate: Date at which the code becomes valid (inclusive).
help.endDate: Date at which the validity of the code ends. The code is valid on that date until midnight (hours are truncated). Must be greater than (or equal to) START_DATE.
help.parentInternalCode: Reference of the parent code in multi-level lists. Used together with STD_CODES_GROUP.PARENT_GROUP_CODE to find the code in STD_CODES(GROUP_CODE, INTERNAL_CODE).
help.comments: Internal comments. Optional. Not shown to end-users.
help.codeValueDate: Value of the element when the type set in STD_CODES_GROUP.VALUE_TYPE is ''D'' (Date).
help.codeValueString: Value of the element when the type set in STD_CODES_GROUP.VALUE_TYPE is ''S'' (String).
help.codeValueBool: Value of the element when the type set in STD_CODES_GROUP.VALUE_TYPE is ''B'' (Boolean).
help.codeValueNumber: Value of the element when the type set in STD_CODES_GROUP.VALUE_TYPE is ''N'' (Number)
